(c) lee Christ-life yields nothing to the kingdom of evil

The Pharisees yielded almost all the world. In the province of humanity all the Gentiles, all the Samaritam, many of the Sadducees also, all the common people, all the afflicted, were freely yielded up as Satan's lawful prey. In the province of letters and art all the culture of the Gentiles was given to him without so much as a wistful glance. In the province of human qualities all those which were not needed for the keeping of the law were delivered over to death.
